.TH clearok 3
.SH NAME
\*Lclearok\*O \- Enables screen clearing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lint clearok(\*Vwin\*L, \*Vbf\*L)
    WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L;
    bool \*Vbf\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "clearok subroutine"
If \*Lbf\*O is TRUE, the next call to \*Lrefresh\*O(3)
for the specified
window will clear the window completely and redraw the entire
window without changing the original screen's contents.
This is useful when the contents of the screen are uncertain.
If the window is \*Lstdscr\*O, the entire screen is redrawn.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Lclearok\*O
function returns OK on success and ERR on error.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
\*Lrefresh\*O(3)
.EQ
